The SITEMANAGER IV provides the ability to monitor UPS and environmental data and set alarm thresholds based on customer requirements. Also other non-computer devices may be managed via this unit, using the digital input channel for status indication and alarm management. The SITEMANAGER IV meets CE EMV and the directive WEEE 2002/96/EC and RoHS 2002/95/EC and the German implementation of the electrical and electronic equipment law. The SITEMANAGER IV is the successor of the SITEMANAGER 2 & 3 an a versatile management computer for racks, to manage your UPS, Environmental and Power sensors and dry contacts. The device can be operated via the web browser interface to switch 8 outputs (up to 4A AC), and to monitor 8 digital (drycontact alarm input and/or output) and 8 analogue inputs (0-10V, 0-20mA and/ or 4-20mA sensors). The device has a space saving design suited for 19” rack installations.Users can individually configure alarms and automatic reactions. The SITEMANAGER II/IV is fully UNMS compatible - fully manageable through UNMS software. (UNMS not included). The user can individually control the 8 230V outlets and react to alarms from the digital inputs or analog measuring devices. RCCMD server included, to manage remote shutdown of network computers.The SITEMANAGER IV provides the ability to monitor UPS and environmental data and set alarm thresholds based on customer requirements. Also other non-computer devices may be managed via this unit, using the digital input channel for status indication and alarm management.The SITEMANAGER IV meets CE EMV and the directive WEEE 2002/96/EC and RoHS 2002/95/EC and the German implementation of the electrical and electronic equipment law.

The SITEMONITOR II manages via the embedded Webserver and the networking tools UPSMON, UPSMAN, RCCMD up to 64 digital inputs. With the use of 2 SM_64_CON_R Terminals (connected toAUX 1 and AUX 2 of the SITEMONITOR) the user may configure up to 8 outputs, eg. as reaction to the input alarms or the 64 contacts. The configuration interface is simple and easy to use. Via the input logic the user can monitor and manages combinde events (AND/OR logic) in case of alarms. Any kind of digital contact sensor may be monitored, e.g. smoke, gas detectors, glass break sensors, fire detectors etc. With the SM_64_CON_R terminal any kind of output may be switched - fully programmable!The SITEMONITOR II meets CE EMV and the directive WEEE 2002/96/EC and RoHS 2002/95/EC and the German implementation of the Electrical and Electronic Equipment Law.
